 most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Horne was born in 1470, in Bapton, Wiltshire, England. She married Richard Pyle in 1500, in Wiltshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1500, in Wiltshire, England."},"et":{"1470–after 1500":"1470–pärast 1500","1470–1515":"1470–1515","1500–1561":"1500–1561","1470–1500":"1470–1500","after 1500":"pärast 1500","1500":"1500","1561":"1561","1470":"1470","1515":"1515","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Bapton, Wiltshire, England":"Bapton, Wiltshire, England","Babton, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1470–after 1500":"1470–1500 jälkeen","1470–1515":"1470–1515","1500–1561":"1500–1561","1470–1500":"1470–1500","after 1500":"1500 jälkeen","1500":"1500","1561":"1561","1470":"1470","1515":"1515","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Bapton, Wiltshire, England":"Bapton, Wiltshire, England","Babton, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1470–after 1500":"1470–après 1500","1470–1515":"1470–1515","1500–1561":"1500–1561","1470–1500":"1470–1500","after 1500":"après 1500","1500":"1500","1561":"1561","1470":"1470","1515":"1515","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre","Bapton, Wiltshire, England":"Bapton, Wiltshire, Angleterre","Babton, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Horne est née en 1470, à Bapton, Wiltshire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Richard Pyle en 1500, à Wiltshire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée après 1500, à Wiltshire, Angleterre."},"de":{"1470–after 1500":"1470–nach 1500","1470–1515":"1470–1515